# Yemen Flow Hub Frontend Rules

Read `../AGENTS.md` before taking any action. It is the single file of truth.

## Git
Frontend code lives in two repos. After every change, commit to both:
1. `frontend/` → `git@github.com:ultimate-eg/yemen-flow-hub-frontend.git` (team repo)
2. Root `/` → `git@github.com:majedsiefalnasr/yemen-flow-hub.git` (monorepo, `git add frontend/<files>`)

Commit format: `type(scope): description`
Never add or commit generated artifacts from `graphify-out/`, `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/`, or `_bmad-output/test-artifacts/`. Keep them local only.

## Stack
Nuxt 4, Vue 4, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, shadcn-vue, Pinia, VeeValidate, Zod

## Non-negotiable UI Rules

### RTL is default
```html
<html dir="rtl" lang="ar">
```
All layouts, tables, sidebars, and forms are RTL. Never mirror LTR layouts.

### Desktop-first
Responsive degradation at ≤ 600px. Not mobile-first progressive enhancement.

### No business logic in components
```typescript
// ✅ Correct — logic in composable
const { submitVote } = useVoting()

// ❌ Never — logic directly in <script setup>
const result = await $fetch('/api/voting/...')
if (result.votes > 3) { ... }
```

### Canonical status enum
Use only values from `../AGENTS.md`. Never use `INTERNAL_REJECTED`, `WAITING_SWIFT`, or any unlisted value.

### Data Entry simplified statuses
Map internal statuses using the table from `../docs/01-workflow-and-business-rules.md`.
Centralize this mapping in `constants/statusMap.ts` — never inline it.

### Design tokens (non-negotiable)
```ts
// constants/design.ts
export const colors = {
  background: '#f5f5f7',
  surface: '#ffffff',
  primaryText: '#1d1d1f',
  border: '#d2d2d7',
  primaryBlue: '#0071e3',
  approvedGreen: '#34c759',
  rejectedRed: '#ff3b30',
  pendingAmber: '#ff9f0a',
  votingIndigo: '#5856d6',
  swiftCyan: '#32ade6',
  lockedGray: '#8e8e93',
}
```
No inline hex values that differ from these. No gradients. No glassmorphism.

### Support claim heartbeat
```typescript
// useClaimHeartbeat.ts
onMounted(() => {
  interval = setInterval(() => {
    $fetch(`/api/workflow/${requestId}/claim-support-review/heartbeat`, { method: 'POST' })
  }, 60_000)
})
onUnmounted(() => clearInterval(interval))
```

### Voting optimistic UI
After vote submission, show result optimistically. On `VOTING_SESSION_CLOSED` error, revert and notify.

### Locked state visual
- Disable all action buttons
- Show `#8e8e93` lock badge
- Use `#f5f5f7` field backgrounds

